# Security rules

This app performs destructive actions. Treat security as a product requirement.

## Non-negotiables

- Never ask for the user's X password.
- Use OAuth 2.0 Authorization Code with PKCE.
- Keep tokens server-side only.
- Encrypt tokens at rest.
- Never expose tokens to browser JavaScript.
- Never delete directly from client code.
- Never delete without a dry run.
- Never delete without server-side queue hash verification.
- Never delete without server-side typed deletion verse verification.
- Never parse or display DMs from an archive upload.

## Destructive endpoint checklist

Before creating a live deletion job, verify:

- Authenticated app user
- Connected account ownership
- Token belongs to displayed X account
- Queue generated server-side
- Dry run exists and is current
- Queue hash matches
- Sample review is complete when required
- Typed verse matches expected verse
- Final literal line matches exact destructive action
- CSRF protection passes
- Rate limits are applied

## Logging rules

Log job status and post IDs attempted. Do not log access tokens, refresh tokens, raw archive files, or full post text by default.
